            <title>[CAMEL-3356] Hard coded locale in Bindy DatePatternFormat</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3356</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As reported by a user from the community (&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Bindy-Dateformat-Parsing-exception-td3276981.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Bindy-Dateformat-Parsing-exception-td3276981.html&lt;/a&gt;), the locale of SimpeDateFormat in bindy&apos;s DatePatternFormat class is hard coded to FRANCE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
